  "response": "Pakistan's economic system is a mixed economy, which combines elements of both capitalism and socialism. Here are some key details:\n\n1. Mixed Economic System:\n- Allows both private and public sector participation\n- Private businesses can operate alongside government-controlled industries\n- Some key sectors like defense, utilities, and infrastructure are predominantly government-controlled\n\n2. Historical Development:\n- Since independence in 1947, Pakistan has undergone several economic transformations\n- Initially adopted a socialist-oriented economic model under early governments\n- In the 1960s, began transitioning towards a more market-oriented approach\n- In the 1980s and 1990s, further liberalized the economy with privatization and market reforms\n- Currently maintains a mixed economic structure with ongoing reforms\n\n3. Current Economic Characteristics:\n- Private sector plays a significant role in economic activities\n- Government maintains regulatory and strategic economic planning\n- Significant agricultural and manufacturing sectors\n- Developing industrial and service sectors\n\n4. Key Economic Sectors:\n- Agriculture\n- Textiles\n- Manufacturing\n- Services\n- Remittances from overseas workers\n\nThe mixed economic system has been evolving since independence, with significant shifts occurring in different decades, but maintaining a balance between state involvement and private enterprise.",
